# Cyrius Dependency Management — Vidya Reference
# How cyrius.toml deps work, stdlib vs project deps, and the dep resolution flow.
# 2026-04-15

[[entries]]
name = "cyrius_toml_overview"
description = "cyrius.cyml is the project manifest — declares build config, stdlib deps, and external deps (legacy cyrius.toml is a fallback)"
category = "cyrius"
---
Every Cyrius project has a cyrius.cyml at the root (CYML = TOML header +
markdown body, v5.0.0+). Legacy cyrius.toml is still read as a fallback.
Three sections matter for deps:

    [package]
    name = "myproject"
    version = "0.1.0"

    [deps]
    stdlib = ["string", "fmt", "alloc", "io", "vec", "str", "syscalls", "assert"]

    [deps.sakshi]
    git = "https://github.com/MacCracken/sakshi.git"
    tag = "2.0.0"
    modules = ["dist/sakshi.cyr"]

The [deps] section has two forms:
1. stdlib = [...] — copies modules from the installed Cyrius stdlib into lib/
2. [deps.NAME] — clones a git repo at a tag and copies specific module files

Running `cyrius deps` resolves both. All resolved files land in lib/ as
absolute symlinks (falls back to copy). The compiler auto-includes them
via the dep include list. Namespaced deps map to lib/{depname}_{basename};
if the basename matches depname, lib/{depname}.cyr alias is also created.

[[entries]]
name = "stdlib_deps"
description = "stdlib deps copy .cyr files from the installed Cyrius distribution into the project lib/"
category = "cyrius"
---
stdlib = ["string", "fmt", "alloc", "io", "vec", "str", "syscalls", "assert"]

Each name maps to lib/{name}.cyr in the Cyrius installation. `cyrius deps` copies
these files into the project's lib/ directory. The compiler then auto-includes them.

Common stdlib modules and what they provide:

  string   — strlen, streq, memeq, memcpy, memset, memchr, strchr, atoi, strstr
  fmt      — fmt_int, fmt_hex, fmt_sprintf (with bufsz), fmt_printf, fmt_float
  alloc    — bump allocator (alloc_init, alloc, alloc_reset), arena allocator
  io       — file_read_all, file_write_all, file_exists, dir_list
  vec      — dynamic array (vec_new, vec_push, vec_get, vec_pop, vec_find)
  str      — heap-allocated strings (str_from, str_cat, str_split, str_builder)
  syscalls — Linux syscall wrappers (open, close, read, write, fork, exec, etc.)
  assert   — test assertions (assert_eq, assert, test_group, assert_summary)
  net      — TCP sockets (tcp_socket, sockaddr_in)
  thread   — threads, mutex, channels (thread_create, mutex_lock, chan_send)
  hashmap  — string-keyed hash table (map_new, map_set, map_get, map_has)
  json     — JSON parser
  toml     — TOML parser
  cyml     — CYML parser (TOML header + markdown body)
  tls      — TLS client via libssl.so.3 (dynlib bridge)

IMPORTANT: alloc_init() must be called before any alloc() calls. Most stdlib
modules that allocate (vec, str, hashmap, json, toml) require it.

[[entries]]
name = "project_deps"
description = "Project deps clone a git repo at a pinned tag and copy specific module files into lib/"
category = "cyrius"
---
External dependencies are declared as [deps.NAME] sections in cyrius.toml:

    [deps.sigil]
    git = "https://github.com/MacCracken/sigil.git"
    tag = "2.9.0"
    modules = ["dist/sigil.cyr"]

Fields:
  git     — repository URL (validated: shell metacharacters rejected)
  tag     — git tag to clone (pinned version — no floating branches)
  modules — list of .cyr files relative to repo root to import
  path    — (optional) local path instead of git clone

Resolution flow:
1. `cyrius deps` reads the [deps.NAME] section
2. Clones to $CYRIUS_HOME/deps/{name}/{tag}/ (shallow, cached)
3. For each module in modules[]:
   - Source: {clone_dir}/{module_path}
   - Dest:   lib/{depname}_{basename}  (always namespaced)
   - Creates absolute symlink (falls back to copy if symlink fails)
4. If basename matches depname (e.g. sigil.cyr for [deps.sigil]),
   also creates lib/{depname}.cyr alias for canonical include path
5. Adds to auto-include list

Consumers include via: include "lib/sigil.cyr"
The namespaced form (lib/sigil_sigil.cyr) also works but the alias is preferred.

[[entries]]
name = "dep_bundle_pattern"
description = "Multi-file deps must bundle into a single dist/*.cyr file for distribution"
category = "cyrius"
---
Cyrius has no multi-file module system — the compiler processes a single compilation
unit (one file, with includes expanded). External deps with multiple source files
must bundle them into a single .cyr file.

The standard pattern (used by sigil, patra, yukti, mabda, sankoch):

1. Create scripts/bundle.sh that concatenates sources in dependency order
2. Strip include lines (grep -v "^include ")
3. Add a header with version, source URL, license, usage
4. Output to dist/{name}.cyr

Example bundle.sh:
    for f in src/types.cyr src/core.cyr src/api.cyr; do
        echo "# --- $(basename "$f") ---"
        grep -v "^include " "$ROOT/$f"
    done > "$ROOT/dist/mylib.cyr"

Then cyrius.toml references: modules = ["dist/mylib.cyr"]

Common gotchas when bundling:
- Duplicate variable names across files: Cyrius has no block scoping for
  if/elif, so `var x` in one elif and `var x` in another elif within the
  same function collide. Hoist to function top and reassign.
- Reserved words as variable names: `match`, `type`, `break` etc. Rename.
- Large static arrays (var buf[262144]): will overflow the 1MB output buffer.
  Heap-allocate with alloc() instead.
- File ordering: types/constants first, then low-level, then high-level, then
  public API last.

[[entries]]
name = "cyrius_update_flow"
description = "cyrius update refreshes lib/ and .cyrius-toolchain from the installed Cyrius version"
category = "cyrius"
---
`cyrius update` does two things:

1. Copies all .cyr files from the installed Cyrius stdlib into lib/
   (reads $CYRIUS_HOME/current to find the installed version)
2. Updates .cyrius-toolchain to match the installed version

This is the primary upgrade mechanism. When a new Cyrius version is installed:
  $ cyrius update

After updating, re-run `cyrius deps` to refresh external deps if needed.

The .cyrius-toolchain file pins the minimum Cyrius version for CI reproducibility.
`cyrius init` creates it from VERSION; `cyrius update` keeps it current.

As of v5.0.0, the canonical manifest is cyrius.cyml (CYML = TOML header +
markdown body); legacy cyrius.toml is still read as a fallback.

[[entries]]
name = "existing_deps_registry"
description = "Current Cyrius ecosystem deps: 6 external libraries available via cyrius.cyml"
category = "cyrius"
---
As of v5.6.43, six external libraries are available as deps (pinned in cyrius.cyml):

NOTE: `cyrius deps` resolves DIRECT deps only — transitive deps are
not auto-fetched. Consumers must list every transitive dep in their
own manifest. Pinned for the v5.7.x cycle (post-RISC-V port) — see
roadmap §v5.7.x for the recursive-walker + lockfile + closest-wins
fix. Workaround until then: hand-list all transitives.


  sakshi (2.0.0)  — Tracing and error handling. Two profiles:
                     sakshi.cyr (stderr-only, minimal) and
                     sakshi_full.cyr (ring buffer, UDP, span stack).
                     Zero heap allocation. Zero external deps.

  patra (1.8.3)   — Structured storage and SQL queries. Bumped at
                     cyrius v5.6.20 from 1.5.5 to 1.6.0 for blob
                     support (sit consumer). Bumped again at v5.6.40
                     from 1.6.0 to 1.8.3 — INSERT OR IGNORE syntax
                     (1.7.0), STR-keyed B+ tree indexes (1.7.1), 4KB
                     page-slab allocator + word-at-a-time _memeq256 +
                     prepared statements (`patra_prepare` /
                     `patra_exec_prepared` / `patra_query_prepared` /
                     `patra_finalize`) (1.8.2), fmt/lint/doc cleanup
                     (1.8.3). Folded in cleanly after v5.6.21's
                     bare-truthy-after-fn-call codegen fix unblocked
                     the idiomatic `if (r)` pattern across patra
                     source. Bundled: dist/patra.cyr.

  sigil (2.9.3)   — System-wide trust verification (SHA-256/512/SHAKE,
                     Ed25519, HMAC, HKDF, TPM, AES-NI, SHA-NI).
                     Bundled: dist/sigil.cyr. v2.9.0 added HKDF +
                     SHAKE-128/256; v2.9.1 consumers use AES-NI
                     cleanly after v5.5.21 fixed SSE m128 16-byte
                     alignment; v2.9.2 added SHA-NI CPUID probe +
                     dispatch entry point; v2.9.3 landed the SHA-NI
                     compress (drop-in replacement for software
                     SHA-256, ~80x throughput win on x86_64 SHA-NI
                     hosts; surfaced by sit v0.6.4's perf review).
                     Bumped 2.9.0 → 2.9.3 at cyrius v5.6.43.

  yukti (2.1.1)   — Device abstraction layer for AGNOS.
                     Bundled: dist/yukti.cyr and dist/yukti-core.cyr
                     (kernel-safe core profile).

  mabda (2.5.0)   — GPU foundation (wgpu-native shim, compute dispatch).
                     Bundled: dist/mabda.cyr. Note: 141KB+ bundle
                     requires input_buf >= 256KB (raised in v3.4.19).
                     v2.5.0 depends on the u64-keyed hashmap added
                     in cyrius v5.5.20 (map_u64_* family).

  sankoch (2.1.0) — Lossless compression (LZ4, DEFLATE, zlib, gzip).
                     Bundled: dist/sankoch.cyr. Bumped 2.0.1 → 2.0.3
                     at cyrius v5.6.35 (deflate-encoder fixes for
                     sit-tree-shaped inputs); bumped 2.0.3 → 2.1.0 at
                     cyrius v5.6.43 (DEFLATE compress perf — pre-
                     reversed dynamic Huffman codes, 8-byte word-
                     compare match extension, ring-buffer absolute-
                     position match-finder; wire-format byte-for-byte
                     identical, no API change).

To add any of these to your project:
    [deps.sigil]
    git = "https://github.com/MacCracken/sigil.git"
    tag = "2.9.3"
    modules = ["dist/sigil.cyr"]

Then: cyrius deps
